Q1) Explain Type casting and its types with examples?
Answer1: 
		Convert a value from one data type to another data type is known as type casting.
		Conversion of one data type to another:
			eg. int to float
				or float to double etc
				
Q3) Explain the difference between local and instance variables?
Answer3: 
		An instance variable is a variable that is declared in a class but outside a method,
		while the local variable is a variable declared within a method or a constructor.
		Thus, this is the main difference between instance variable and local variable.